content: Sentencing day for Emily Dearden. In 2013 the former NYPD psychologist shot her husband in the head while he slept. In a lawsuit Kenneth Dearden claims the shooting was because of an affair his wife was having. Today he told her, "I try to remember that I'm lucky to be alive." Dearden will serve 3 and-a-half years in prison as part of a plea deal.
name: Marcus Solis

content: Recognize these items? The gold watch and ring were among skeletal remains found wrapped in a carpet at 165 Bruce Avenue in Yonkers. I covered the story on Eyewitness News earlier this month.  More than a week later, the body is still unidentified so  the Yonkers Police Department is asking for the public's help.  Anyone with information is urged to contact the Major Case Squad.
name: Marcus Solis
title: Timeline Photos

content: The angry mother of a fifth grader in the Bronx is demanding action after a school principal allegedly pushed her daughter to the ground.  Vanessa Roman says the principal of PS 132 flew into a rage over the bad behavior of a class.  The girl says she bruised her shoulder against a desk while falling.  Roman has filed a police report and the New York City Department of Education is investigating.
name: Marcus Solis

content: Police have identified the victim in last night's freak, fatal accident in Port Chester. 14-year old Chris Aguilar was killed when he fell through the roof and down an elevator shaft of an abandoned hospital.  A group of teens were on the roof--a common hangout spot--when the incident occurred. Police estimate Aguilar plunged 60 feet.
name: Marcus Solis
title: Timeline Photos

content: Terrifying moments for an 11-year old girl in Yonkers. Jaelyn Rodriguez was mauled by two bull mastiffs while she was on her way to school. She suffered bites to her arms, legs and torso. A Good Samaritan was able to put the girl in his car and drive her to a hospital. Police put down the dogs and their owner is being questioned.
name: Marcus Solis

content: Police on the scene of a double murder in East New York. A 27-year old man and a 23-year old woman were ambushed as they got into an SUV around 4:50am.  Over a dozen shots fired at the car. The victims were pronounced dead at the scene. Police are searching for the gunman.

content: A Rockland County mother and her 3 children remain hospitalized after they were hit by car in Monsey yesterday. The driver may have been cut off by a cab and police are investigating the crash as a road rage incident.  62-year old Albert Gomez has been charged with assault.  In the meantime residents are angry about the lack of sidewalks along that stretch of Route 59.  The state DOT says it will improve signage immediately and is working on long term solutions for the area.
name: Marcus Solis

content: Drag racing has been a problem in Yonkers for decades. In 2015 a dispute between two groups led to the shooting death of Mike Nolan, a rising minor league pitching prospect. Now the city has enacted a new law--thought of by the Nolan family. Effective July 1 anyone caught drag racing will have their car confiscated.
